1. Executive Overview
The Two Step Challenge is Doji Funding's classic evaluation product featuring a dual-phase approach that provides the firmest trader validation. With two separate profit targets spread across two phases, it offers maximum freedoms and the highest scaling potential at 10x.
1.1 Target Audience
All trader levels, from beginners seeking a structured evaluation path to professionals who want the highest possible scaling ceiling and maximum trading freedoms.
1.2 Key Differentiators vs One Step
Dual-Phase Validation: Two separate targets provide a double filter, significantly reducing the firm's risk exposure.
Maximum Freedoms: News trading allowed, all EA types permitted, copy trading unrestricted, all instruments available.
10x Scaling Potential: Highest scaling ceiling of any Doji product (vs 5x for One Step, 2x for Instant).
Lower Base Pricing at Scale: At $100K, the Two Step costs $399 vs $499 for One Step.
Minimum 1% Payout Threshold: Most accessible payout requirement of any product.
Promo Code Support: Percentage or fixed-amount discount codes with a floor at 30% of base price.
2. Dual-Phase Architecture
2.1 Phase Structure
The evaluation is split into two sequential phases. The trader must pass Phase 1 before entering Phase 2. Both phases share the same risk parameters but have independent profit targets.

Attribute	Phase 1	Phase 2
Profit Target Range	5% - 12%	3% - 8%
Default Target	8%	5%
Min Trading Days	60% of total days	40% of total days
Risk Parameters	Shared with Phase 2	Same as Phase 1
Account Reset	N/A	Balance reset to initial if Phase 1 passed

IMPORTANT: Min trading days are split 60/40 between Phase 1 and Phase 2. Example: 10 total min days = Phase 1 requires 6 days, Phase 2 requires 4 days.
2.2 Phase Transition Logic
// Phase 1 -> Phase 2 transition
if (phase1.profitReached && phase1.minDaysMet
    && phase1.consistencyPassed && phase1.noBreaches) {
  account.balance = account.initialBalance; // Reset
  account.phase = 2;
  account.phase2StartDate = NOW();
}

// Phase 2 -> Funded transition
if (phase2.profitReached && phase2.minDaysMet
    && phase2.consistencyPassed && phase2.noBreaches) {
  account.status = 'FUNDED';
  account.fundedDate = NOW();
  enablePayoutSystem(account);
}
