3.2 Customizable Parameters
Parameter	Range	Default	Step
Phase 1 Profit Target	5% - 12%	8%	1%
Phase 2 Profit Target	3% - 8%	5%	1%
Daily Loss Limit	3% - 8%	5%	1%
Maximum Loss Limit	6% - 15%	10%	1%
Profit Split	70% - 90%	80%	5%
Min Trading Days (Total)	5 - 20 days	10 days	1 day
Consistency Rule	10% - 50%	30%	10%
Payout Frequency	Monthly / Bi-Weekly / Weekly	Bi-Weekly	N/A
Daily Loss Calc Type	Intraday / EOD / Static	Intraday	N/A
Max Loss Calc Type	Intraday / EOD / Static	Intraday	N/A
3.3 Loss Calculation Types
Intraday (Cheapest): Real-time tick-by-tick monitoring. Breach = immediate suspension. Applies identically to both phases.
End of Day (Standard): Limits evaluated only at market close. Intraday fluctuations ignored. Baseline pricing.
Static (Premium): Daily loss fixed at start-of-day balance; max loss fixed at initial account balance. Most expensive option.
3.4 Loss Type Pricing (Two Step Specific)
Loss Calc Type	Daily Loss Adj	Max Loss Adj	Combined Range
Intraday	-$19	-$19	-$38 (cheapest)
End of Day	$0	$0	$0 (baseline)
Static	+$29	+$29	+$58 (premium)

NOTE: Two Step loss type adjustments are larger than One Step (-$19 vs -$15 for intraday, +$29 vs +$25 for static) because the dual-phase structure amplifies the impact over a longer evaluation period.
3.5 Optional Add-Ons
Add-On	Price	Description	vs One Step
Overnight Holding	+$25	Hold through daily close	+$6 vs 1-Step ($19)
Overweek Holding	+$39	Hold through weekends. Enforces min 5 days.	+$10 vs 1-Step ($29)

OVERWEEK CONSTRAINT: Enabling Overweek Holding automatically sets the minimum trading days to 5 if currently lower.
3.6 Payout Frequency Pricing
Payout frequency is a monetized parameter:

Frequency	Additional Cost	Description
Monthly	$0 (included)	Standard payout cycle, no additional cost
Bi-Weekly	+$29	Payouts every two weeks
Weekly	+$59	Fastest payout cycle, premium pricing

WEEKLY PAYOUT CONSTRAINT: Weekly payout caps the consistency rule at 30% maximum.
 
4. Pricing Engine
4.1 Pricing Formula
The formula is identical in structure to One Step, but with different coefficients:

FINAL = max(
  Base + Difficulty + Split + Options + LossType
  + EqualLossSurcharge + PayoutFreqAdj,
  Base * 0.5
)

// With promo code:
PROMO PRICE = max(FINAL - PromoDiscount, Base * 0.3)
4.2 Difficulty Adjustment Rules
The combined target (Phase 1 + Phase 2) is used for target-based adjustments:

Condition	Adjustment	Direction	Logic
Combined Target < 10%	+$15 per 1% below 10%	Price increases	Lower total target = easier
Combined Target > 12%	-$10 per 1% above 12%	Price decreases	Higher total target = harder
Daily Loss > 5%	+$50 per 1% above 5%	Price increases	Wider daily = more forgiving
Daily Loss < 5%	-$25 per 1% below 5%	Price decreases	Tighter daily = stricter
Max Loss > 10%	+$45 per 1% above 10%	Price increases	More drawdown room
Max Loss < 10%	-$20 per 1% below 10%	Price decreases	Less room = harder
Min Days < 10	+$10 per day below 10	Price increases	Fewer days = less validation
Consistency < 45%	-$3 per % below 45%	Price decreases	Looser consistency
Consistency > 45%	+$3 per % above 45%	Price increases	Stricter consistency
4.3 Split Adjustment
The split adjustment baseline for Two Step is 80% (vs 70% for One Step):

splitAdjustment = (split - 80) * $6

Examples:
  Split 70% => (70 - 80) * 6 = -$60
  Split 80% => (80 - 80) * 6 = $0
  Split 85% => (85 - 80) * 6 = +$30
  Split 90% => (90 - 80) * 6 = +$60

NOTE: The per-percent rate is $6 for Two Step vs $4 for One Step.
4.4 Equal Loss Surcharge
When Daily Loss equals Max Loss, a flat surcharge of +$100 is applied (same as One Step).
4.5 Payout Frequency Adjustment
payoutAdj = { monthly: $0, biweekly: +$29, weekly: +$59 }
4.6 Promo Code System
Identical to One Step. Percentage or fixed-amount discounts. Floor at 30% of base price.

promoDiscount = (type === 'percent') ? total * value / 100 : fixedValue
promoFinal = max(total - promoDiscount, basePrice * 0.3)
4.7 Pricing Examples
Example 1 - Default Config ($50K):
Account: $50,000 | P1 Target: 8% | P2 Target: 5%
Daily: 5% | Max: 10% | Split: 80% | Days: 10 | Consistency: 30%
Loss Types: Both Intraday | No add-ons | Payout: Bi-Weekly

Combined Target = 13% (> 12%: -$10)
Base Price:         $249
Difficulty:         -$10 (target 13% > 12%: -$10)
                    -$45 (consistency 30% < 45%: -$45)
Split Adj:          +$0  (80-80)*6
Loss Type:          -$38 (-19 + -19)
Equal Loss:         +$0
Payout Freq:        +$29 (bi-weekly)
Options:            +$0
-------------------------------
TOTAL:              $185
